summary: Gotta admit, I was not expecting to love Crowley as much as I do because I’m not into the whole dark-edgy-demon thing, nor am I...
body:
Gotta admit, I was not expecting to love Crowley as much as I do because I’m not into the whole dark-edgy-demon thing, nor am I into excusing the type of bad acts that demons are usually depicted as getting up to.

But then it turned out that he’s really more of a shenanigans and mischief type, with a better moral compass than most anyone else on the show. So I love him. It was a very good subverting of my expectations (I’ve never read Good Omens or really encountered it’s fandom before the show, so I went in blind).

And this might sound weird, but he really suits a Megamind AU. “Bad” mostly because that’s what other people decided he should be.
